an life, but changes are occurring in this area as well. From Grandmother to Granddaughter is a vivid and authentic portrait of today's El Salvador that convincingly illustrates how individual lives can reflect the larger changes within a society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aOral history. 0aWomenxSocial conditionsx20th centuryxEl Salvador. 0aWomenzEl SalvadorxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  abiographical.  abiography.  achildhood.  achildren.  acoming of age.  adomestic.  ael salvador.  afamilia.  afamily life.  afamily living.  afamily relationships.  afemale stories.  afeminism.  afeminist.  agranddaughter.  agrandmother.  agrandparents.  agrowing up.  alatin america.  alife story.  aparenting.  aparents.  asouth america.  aspanish language.  atrue story.  awomens issues.  awomens stories.1 aLeal, Gloria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPineda, Marta, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092450540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520924505423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520924505.jpg  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles